{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"12a4f61f-3999-47e6-9bc1-e213b7c098e0","content":"Update these three files:\n\n**1. `.csproj`** — change the TFM:\n```xml\n<TargetFramework>net11.0</TargetFramework>\n```\n\n**2. `global.json`** — pin the new SDK:\n```json\n{ \"sdk\": { \"version\": \"11.0.100\" } }\n```\n\n**3. `Dockerfile`** — update base images:\n```dockerfile\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/aspnet:11.0 AS base\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/sdk:11.0 AS build\n```\n\nThen run:\n```bash\ndotnet restore\ndotnet build\n```\n\nCheck for any breaking changes in the [.NET 11 migration guide](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/dotnet/core/compatibility/11.0) and update any NuGet packages (e.g., `Microsoft.AspNetCore.*`, `Microsoft.Extensions.*`) to their 11.x versions.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"1ded1407-b3a7-4d43-99bb-be66ce42758e","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking how to update their .NET project from .NET 10 to .NET 11. This is a straightforward question I can answer from knowledge — no need to explore their codebase since they've described the relevant files.","outputTokens":306,"requestId":"6829:28D016:6330F02:6C07391:69F010AD"},"id":"01c79688-0687-4654-ae4d-0f2cff70bc2e","timestamp":"2026-04-28T01:43:16.481Z","parentId":"ff4df205-35a9-47b4-a715-c9b4df5a29ff"}
